 The National Leader of the All Progressives Congress, Asiwaju Bola Tinubu, has declared his intention to contest for presidency in 2023. Tinubu disclosed this to State House correspondents, on Monday, after a meeting with President Muhammadu Buhari at the Presidential Villa, Abuja. The former Lagos State Governor also stated that he informed President Buhari of his presidential ambition. The former governor said that contesting the presidency was a life-long ambition, adding that he had the capacity to turn things around in the country. 